reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable fit but lower cut than expected
reviews.reviewText: This shirt took almost a month to receive, but I like the look and fit. It's comfortable to wear and the material feels like it will be very breathable when worn during the summer months.The one issue I have is that the cut of the chest is lower than expected. I have several similarly styled Cuban shirts and all of them button up higher on the chest, making it possible to wear a white undershirt. I prefer this as the summer months bring heat and humidity and of course that means sweat, and gnarly pit stains.It's much easier to wash and clean a white undershirt than to have to constantly wash the outer garment.But this shirt is so low cut on the chest that wearing an undershirt is not as much of an option unless you want the undershirt to be visible. And I tried it on with a V-Neck undershirt. It doesn't work.If that doesn't bother you, then this shirt will be fine. You'll probably love it. If wearing an undershirt is preferable to you, then you may be disappointed in this styling as your undershirt will most definitely be visible.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars True to size love this Shirt!!
reviews.reviewText: As I’ve written before and you’ve probably seen many of my reviews because I have this shirt in seven different colors!!!Very seldom do a company have the exact fit true to size but they got it right on the head. Truly soft and stretchy. Comfortable and form fitting but leaves enough for the shirt to be free. Tight on arms. Washable and doesn’t shrink. Button up is a home run and I cannot say enough. Get one for yourself or be like me and get seven in every color available!! I’m a big guy and. 3xl fits me perfect and makes me look slim!! True story!!! Plenty of compliments daily!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Extraordinarily comfortable, great fit, and less expensive than a department store equivalent
reviews.reviewText: Coofandy does it again with another great product! Disclosure: I received this shirt through Vine, but I had already bought several Coofandy products before. I'm thinking of a certain cooking competition TV show: "What would you expect to pay?" I would expect to pay double this MSRP, if not triple. The woven polyester feels almost like cotton, rather than typical smooth polyester.I love this relaxed fit of the "Cuban" style that I gather is meant to be cut a little looser. I'm between an M and L in the chest, and this M seems like a true L. It's cut straight down, which looks a little baggy on my M waist, so I'll probably have a friend give it a bit of a taper.The navy color and collar are splendid for me to pair with a full suit for an elevated business casual year-round. The lapel-like collar seems cut a little lower than the photos show, though I've never before had a shirt with this collar cut. It might just be how the shirt is when fresh out of the package, and it'll "settle in" after a light wash. If not, it's easy to sew a snap button on the inside, a couple of inches above the top button, for a more conservative opening.
